docker network create mynetwork -d bridge: This command creates your own private network for a project.

docker build -t two-tier-backend .: This command is used to create a Docker image from a Dockerfile.

docker network ls: Used to see the list of all networks (Bridge, Host, None).

docker network inspect <network_name>: To see the inside details of a network, like which containers are connected.

docker exec -it <container_id> bash: This command lets you enter inside a running container to check files or run commands.
